'''Bernard Robert Louis Fraisse''' (born August 1956)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/06905983/officers|title=FAREVA UK LIMITED - Officers (free information from Companies House)|publisher=}}</ref> is a French [[billionaire]] businessman, the chairman, founder and 100% owner of [[Fareva]], a French [[pharmaceutical]] company, with annual revenues of $1.4 billion in 2015.<ref name="Forbes">{{cite web|title=The World's Billionaires: Bernard Fraisse|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/bernard-fraisse/|website=Forbes|accessdate=24 January 2017}}</ref>
==Early life== Fraisse has a degree in mechanical engineering.<ref name="Forbes" />
==Career== Fraisse founded Fareva in 1985, and the company now employs 9,500 people.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.capital.fr/a-la-une/classement-des-francais-les-plus-riches/fiches/bernard-fraisse-942832|title=Bernard Fraisse (Fareva)|first=Prisma|last=Media|publisher=}}</ref> Fareva is the largest [[contract manufacturing organization]] (CMO) in France.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pharmaboardroom.com/interviews/interview-bernard-fraisse-president-fareva-france/|title=Interview: Bernard Fraisse - President, Fareva, France|publisher=}}</ref>
==Personal life== Fraisse live in Paris.<ref name="Forbes" />
