{{for|the [[BBC World News]] television programme|World Business Report}} {{Infobox Radio Show | show_name = World Business Report | format = International business and finance news | runtime = 26 minutes | country = [[United Kingdom]] | language = [[English language|English]] | home_station = [[BBC World Service]] | syndicates = | television = | presenter = | starring = | announcer = | creator = | writer = | director = | producer = | executive_producer = | narrated = | record_location = [[Broadcasting House]], [[London]] | first_aired = | last_aired = | num_series = | num_episodes = | audio_format = | opentheme = | endtheme = | website = http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00fvhj7 | Related shows = [[World Business Report]] }}
'''''World Business Report''''' is the [[BBC World Service]]'s international business and finance news programme, broadcast on weekdays at 1632, 1932 and 2232 [[GMT]] and produced at [[Broadcasting House]] in [[London]]. Each programme is 26 minutes long and includes business news, interviews and reports.
